    "submission_date": "2026-05-17",
    "abstract": "Deep RL framework for dynamic portfolio allocation across global equities. SAC learns continuous weights in an MDP with transaction costs, turnover penalties and diversification constraints in the reward. Five configurations (reward type, flat vs hierarchical Dirichlet, constraints, LSTM vs Transformer) evaluated via 16-fold walk-forward on NDX, NKY, SX5E (2003-2026). Competitive mainly in SX5E; no strategy beats Buy&Hold with statistical significance under HAC inference.",
    "domain": "RL",
    "key_claims": [
      "SAC-based RL with hierarchical Dirichlet policy improves risk-adjusted performance vs flat policy",
      "Cash-allowed configurations achieve lower drawdowns and higher IR2 than fully-invested ones",
      "RL strategies outperform Buy&Hold on IR2 in Euro Stoxx 50 across all three macro regimes",
      "Cross-market equal-weight ensemble of RL strategies (LSTM_1) achieves IR2=0.41 vs benchmark 0.34",
      "No RL strategy achieves statistically significant excess returns vs Buy&Hold under HAC-robust inference across all markets"
    ],
    "parsed_at": "2026-05-24T12:00:00Z",
    "arxivist_version": "0.1.0"
  },
